-- Former New York Comptroller Said to Plan Guilty Plea in Pension Fund Probe
-- B y   K a r e n   F r e i f e l d
-- 2010-10-07T12:51:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/ex-new-york-comptroller-hevesi-said-to-plan-guilty-plea-in-corruption-case.html
Former New York Comptroller Alan
Hevesi was taken into custody and will plead guilty to a felony
charge tied to New York Attorney General Andrew Cuomo’s probe of
corruption at the state’s pension fund, a person familiar with
the case said. Hevesi is be arraigned in a Manhattan courtrooom
this morning, said the person, who declined to be identified
because the proceedings aren’t yet public.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Freifeld in New York at 
